<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1811,2092]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
1. Plants often pink to red, rarely green; spores 
<quantity box="[642,743,1811,1832]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="21.0" valueMax="24.0" valueMin="18.0">18–24 µm</quantity>
; capsule elongate-clavate, ± straight, peristome well-developed; sexuality dioicous................................................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spence" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Swartz" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[1358,1450,1839,1861]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Hysterocinetidae" genus="Ptychostomum" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="pallens">
<emphasis box="[1358,1450,1839,1861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">P. pallens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1811,2092]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
- Plants green, yellow-green to brown; spores 
<quantity box="[651,754,1868,1890]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="23.5" valueMax="35.0" valueMin="12.0">12–35 µm</quantity>
, capsule turbinate to clavate, straight or rarely curved, peristome welldeveloped to strongly reduced; sexuality dioicous, autoicous or synoicous ......................................................................................2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1811,2092]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
2. Autoicous; plants green; leaf with distinct limbidium; spores&gt; 
<quantity box="[836,904,1926,1947]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 µm</quantity>
, capsule elongate-clavate, somewhat curved; peristome reduced, cilia absent ........................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hornschuch" authorityYear="1822" baseAuthorityName="Hedwig" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[1343,1451,1955,1976]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Hysterocinetidae" genus="Ptychostomum" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="cernuum">
<emphasis box="[1343,1451,1955,1976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">P. cernuum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1811,2092]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
- Dioicous or synoicous; plants green to yellow-green or brown; leaf limbidium present or absent; spores &lt;
<quantity box="[1214,1279,1984,2005]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 µm</quantity>
; capsule turbinate to short-clavate, typically not curved, peristome well-developed to strongly reduced ......................................................................3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="63" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,1452,1811,2092]" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
<keyLead pageId="2" pageNumber="62">
3. Leaves strongly recurved when wet, with narrow decurrent base; basal most proximal laminal cells somewhat inflated, distinct from cells above; capsule unknown ....................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1848" baseAuthorityName="Mull. Hal." box="[1369,1451,2070,2091]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Hysterocinetidae" genus="Ptychostomum" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="2" pageNumber="62" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="nivale">
<emphasis box="[1369,1451,2070,2091]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="62">P. nivale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1451,159,267]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="63">- Leaves erect but not recurved when wet, base broader, not decurrent; proximal laminal cells not inflated or distinct from cells above; capsules often present .............................................................................................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1451,159,267]" box="[136,1451,217,239]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,217,239]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
4. Leaf margins plane; sexuality dioicous; spores 
<quantity box="[662,763,217,239]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="12.0">12–16 µm</quantity>
, capsule turbinate, cilia present and well-developed ......... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spence" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Hedwig" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[1320,1451,217,238]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Hysterocinetidae" genus="Ptychostomum" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="turbinatum">
<emphasis box="[1320,1451,217,238]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">P. turbinatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1451,159,267]" box="[136,1450,245,267]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
<keyLead box="[136,1450,245,267]" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">
- Leaf margin recurved proximally; sexuality synoicous; spores 
<quantity box="[811,912,245,267]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="24.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="22.0">22–26 µm</quantity>
, capsule clavate, cilia absent ................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1307,1450,246,267]" class="Oligohymenophorea" family="Hysterocinetidae" genus="Ptychostomum" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Scuticociliatida" pageId="3" pageNumber="63" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="mucronatum">
<emphasis box="[1307,1450,246,267]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="63">P. mucronatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
